ic decisions in sequence.","test_description":"Run the real summary-generation backend on representative input datasets and assert extracted key facts in output (numbers, trend direction, incident counts/deploy status) match source values within defined tolerance/format rules; repeat across multiple runs/prompts to catch non-deterministic misstatements.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.12,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.77,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"A complete report — from data collection through email delivery — reaches the configured recipient's inbox correctly.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Failure boundary includes real external delivery path and inbox receipt. MOCK-MISS: in-process mocks cannot validate SMTP/API auth, transport behavior, formatting through provider, or inbox placement. REAL-INFRA: yes—real HTTP/SMTP and actual recipient mailbox behavior are integral. MOCK-HIDE: yes—mock mail clients can pass while real provider rejects/throttles/rewrites. LLM-DEP: not required for this assertion; success criterion is end-to-end delivery correctness, not model quality. MULTI-STEP: even if summary generation exists, this behavior does not require validating multiple model decisions. REJECTION-GATE: rejected Workflow because behavior text emphasizes \"from data collection through email delivery\" and \"reaches ... inbox correctly\" (system E2E transport), not multi-agentic decision chaining.","test_description":"Run the scheduled pipeline (or equivalent trigger) against real reachable source endpoints/test doubles at system boundary and a real email delivery service into a test mailbox; verify final email is received by configured recipient with expected subject/body sections and no pipeline-stage drop.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.09,"System":0.74,"Agentic":0.1,"Workflow":0.06}},{"behavior_i